---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Containing NO — Scrabble Word List & Strategy"
  description="Complete list of Scrabble words containing NO with scores, definitions, and strategic tips. Master NO words for better Scrabble plays."
  keywords="scrabble words containing no, no words scrabble, words with no, scrabble no word list, no scrabble strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Containing NO — Scrabble Word List & Strategy",
    "description": "Complete list of Scrabble words containing NO with scores, definitions, and strategic tips.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-no" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the highest-scoring NO words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top NO words include KNOWLEDGE (18 pts), DENOUNCE (11 pts), ANNOUNCE (10 pts), SNOOKER (11 pts), and MONOPOLY (15 pts). NO appears in 600+ valid Scrabble words." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many Scrabble words contain NO?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Over 600 valid Scrabble words contain NO. Common examples include KNOW, NOTE, SNOW, HONOR, ANNOUNCE, INNOCENT, KNOWLEDGE, and MONOPOLY." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What strategy works best with NO tiles?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "NO is versatile with 600+ words. The KNO- cluster (KNOW, KNOB, KNOCK, KNOT) deploys the K tile. The -NOUNCE pattern (ANNOUNCE, DENOUNCE, PRONOUNCE) builds bingos. SNO- words (SNOW, SNOOKER, SNOOP) use the S tile well. NO- prefix words (NOTE, NOSE, NOBLE) are quick plays." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Letter Pair Content</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Containing NO — Scrabble Word List & Strategy</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">NO is a versatile letter pair appearing in over 600 valid Scrabble words. From common plays like KNOW and NOTE to premium targets like KNOWLEDGE (18 pts) and MONOPOLY (15 pts), NO combines well with high-value consonants. The KNO- cluster deploys the valuable K tile efficiently, while the -NOUNCE pattern builds toward impressive bingos.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top NO Words by Score</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Definition</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KNOWLEDGE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Information understood</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MONOPOLY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Exclusive control</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KNOCK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To strike a door</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SNOOKER</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A billiards game</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">DENOUNCE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To condemn publicly</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ANNOUNCE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To declare publicly</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KNOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">To understand</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KNOB</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A rounded handle</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SNOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Frozen precipitation</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">NOTE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">A written message</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HONOR</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">High respect</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">600+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid NO words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Average score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Common</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Pair frequency</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips for NO Words</h2>

      <p>The KNO- cluster (KNOW, KNOB, KNOCK, KNOT) efficiently deploys the 5-point K tile. The -NOUNCE pattern (ANNOUNCE, DENOUNCE, PRONOUNCE) builds impressive bingos. SNO- words (SNOW, SNOOKER, SNOOP) use the S tile effectively. NO- prefix words (NOTE, NOSE, NOBLE, NORTH) provide quick reliable plays. KNOWLEDGE (18 pts) is the ultimate NO target for competitive scoring.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KNOWLEDGE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KNOCK</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MONOPOLY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SNOOKER</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KNOW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ANNOUNCE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10 pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Key Takeaway</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">NO provides <span class="text-white font-medium">600+ valid words</span> with strong K-tile synergy. KNOWLEDGE (18 pts) and KNOCK (15 pts) are premium targets. KNOW (11 pts) and KNOB (10 pts) are efficient short plays that maximize the K tile alongside this common pair.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-qu" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Containing QU — Essential Scrabble Q Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-multiple-vowels" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words With Multiple Vowels — Scrabble Vowel Dumps</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/four-letter-words-every-player-should-know" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Four-Letter Words Every Scrabble Player Should Know</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every NO word from your tiles — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
